parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electronic Parking Brake (EPB) and Auto Hold System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPB and Auto Hold system can cause the vehicle to unexpectedly stop or lose cruise control, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The EPB and Auto Hold indicator lights illuminate on the dashboard
the cruise control system shuts off
the vehicle slows down or stops unexpectedly
warning lights appear on the dashboard
including the check cruise system light
triangle with an exclamation point
and smart cruise control system notices.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the electronic parking brake warning light and other warning lights to illuminate, potentially leading to a loss of braking performance, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Illumination of the electronic parking brake warning light
illumination of the auto-hold feature warning light
illumination of other unknown warning lights
inability to brake properly
spongy brake pedal
grinding or screeching noise when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Apple CarPlay system can cause inconvenience and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The Apple CarPlay system quits or freezes when using maps
the Apple CarPlay system is unresponsive
the Apple CarPlay system disconnects from the iPhone
the Apple CarPlay system does not display maps or navigation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the auto-dimming rearview mirror can cause distraction and obstruction of the driver's rearview, potentially leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The backup mirror remains on while driving
the auto-dimming rearview mirror does not dim or adjust properly
the mirror is stuck in a certain position or mode.
